metadata.name: Conceptualisation of the unconscious persona.
metadata.description:
C.G. Jung positioned the idea that our persona acts as the complex system between our unconscious mind and our environment around us, with the ultimate goal to conceal our true nature from others. 

This piece illustrates the vivid map of this persona from the perspective of the dreamer looking inwards, introspecting on the fast interplay between their own substrata of ideas and deeply held formulations of their unconscious self.
